{"id": "aa3c3d63e858fc110341ad61730f8572185423242bfb1ee1310a328f03f61e15", "item_id": "cc42e10d94:0", "text": "RenderMan provides full support for typical camera simulation, including two standard projections that PRMan has always supported - perspective and orthographic - as well as features like"}
{"id": "1ba941d3501ce6db76d6ee6d3a9376c41133b979ef3cb82e48d3c6dcbaef6eb5", "item_id": "cc42e10d94:1", "text": "motion blur"}
{"id": "e0181b1d7fdc69199d708d9ea71b7dd75bd04ade5d09afc74350b2970bdf50ec", "item_id": "cc42e10d94:3", "text": "camera effects"}
{"id": "14b5230a503337045fda833709c7d115e4a2222dc90c679f56da0f69b80add4c", "item_id": "cc42e10d94:4", "text": "like Depth of Field and Bokeh."}
{"id": "3a42dcdfd1fb711a1a917aa79e5ab6e29b9360e54eae279419a57445192d3fe2", "item_id": "cc42e10d94:5", "text": "These are supported through projection plugins, enabling the tracing of rays through arbitrary, potentially curved surfaces centered on the viewpoint. The distribution also includes built-in projections -"}
{"id": "0f58b78bc54e0c3e55568ec522fb67be295f3bf726a0d53cef872b7a4272196e", "item_id": "cc42e10d94:6", "text": "sphere"}
{"id": "c871dc1dcab70d1af97e8dd077b730d56f6f603c06173a0df57259a7139e28c3", "item_id": "cc42e10d94:7", "text": "torus"}
{"id": "921178a491aeb0a5fb466ad9aa254afd19c44270452270b6b738b8e0360d4700", "item_id": "cc42e10d94:8", "text": ", and"}
{"id": "05fa0965c7c35c471dd1e8474b76870be2ec1ce535c2b169ab4f3554ab17e436", "item_id": "cc42e10d94:9", "text": "cylinder"}
{"id": "10649aecbe42f0beb69da961242dd4f97b399fba2a64df8de29a421b679613b8", "item_id": "cc42e10d94:10", "text": "- that are compatible with all modes of the raytrace hider."}
{"id": "d8fdaddac09347f519f8255bcfa146273f7e61ad28f44c53264ae335d71bc2a3", "item_id": "cc42e10d94:11", "text": "PxrCamera"}
